Veteran Musician, Sir Victor Uwaifo, has called out award wining Singer, Simi over an alleged intellectual theft. While speaking in an interview at the Annual General Meeting of Copyright Society Of Nigeria COSON, held at Sheraton Hotels, Ikeja, Lagos, Sir, Uwaifo claimed that Simi used the title of his song “Joromi” without giving him credit. According to the Former Commissioner for arts and culture in Edo State, copyright and intellectual property theft is a very serious issue in Nigeria and it must be given urgent attention as it is reducing the creativity of the new generation of musician. He said, the process of making music has now significantly changed from what it used to be in his time, as “more mediocre” are now in the game. His words; When asked if he was going to take any legal action against Simi, he replied: The post Sir Victor Uwaifo Set To Sue Simi Over The Song ‘Joromi’ appeared first on 360Nobs.com.   Follow us on twitter @NigeriaTodayNG Also, Like us on facebook This post was syndicated from 360Nobs.com. Click here to read the full text on the original website.